				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Help! on Erollisi Marr..<a name="60261"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 2:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span> Hello Fellow Divas'!! I am a relatively new 56th bard who just started playing again about 4 months ago, after a three year absence. I have completed all the steps for my epic, except the last <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />  and have scheduled a raid for Saturday the 11th of september for Trakanon! I am very excited and have gotten some support from my (small) guild a few friends and all the people I can talk into helping out with this raid! I have a question reguarding how to check if Trakanon is up. I have read everything I can get my hands on for the last few months on this raid and feel I have a good handle on how to get the job done, but I have only been to Old Sebilis once (two days ago) and was alone and wound up using a gate potion at the zone in point. The map I have is not real good <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" /> and I am not sure where I need to use the stalking probes. Can someone detail where I should do this? (I get lost pretty easy!) Also if there are any folks on Erollisi Marr who would like to come along and have that weekend free for this raid (especially those familiar with the zone!) All comers are welcome! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />  I have tenative commitments from several 65th lvl players and am hoping for a healthy raid force size...but will not know for sure until the day actually arrives. I hope to have a necromancer (for DMF buff) a mage (for CoTH) 2 65th Bards (who have been there done that) a 65th SK MT along with various &quot;Nukers&quot; and healers, plus a few more tanks and a smattering of other folks of various levels and class (50+ lvl) if all goes well Trak #1 is already down and it is just a matter of UNB spawn timing. otherwise it will turn out to be two raids to get the deed done (I realize that if all show up I will have massive over-kill. but my research has shown that better safe than sorry with Trakanon and if not hopefully I will still get enough there to get the job done) I appreciate all the posts on this site that have helped me get this far and thank you all for such great support!! Hopefully I will be a new blue-note Bard on Erollisi Marr in less than two weeks!! This will be the culmination of over four years of striving for Loredic Windsong and I am very excited at the prospect of this raid!!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
