				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Help! on Erollisi Marr..<a name="61499"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 11 04 9:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well the raid went down today (saturday)...I had contacted quite a few people and had a pretty small percentage of the ones I contacted show up...but I did have a real quality core group of players that did show (I suspected this to be the case..hence all the contacts!!) I was fortunate to get some real awsome help on the open pick-up raid channel on Erollisi-Marr, this in addition to my great core group! I found that a group camped UDB friday night and apprently took the UDB out at around 8:00 pacific time. I started forming up raid around 9:00 saturday hoping for some fortunate spawn timing. We headed into Sebilis around 12:30ish after some in the group completed key quest. I discovered from a tracker in the group that as we were fighting through to the lair the UDB spawned! We killed all the mobs on the way and in the lair..then I did my turn in and spawned Trak! I had about 3 groups and trak went down real fast! He bannished the MT, a 65sk (Qezam) but our 65th mage (Silverelm) CotH him back almost instently!  About three of our raid died in the melee but it was all over in less than a minute! Now Erollisi Marr has a brand new blue-note bard and I want to thank all the folks that helped me so much! I met some great folks in a LDoN group about a week earlier and just about the whole group showed and brought a few friends to boot! Thanks to these folks as well as the ones who joind from the pick-up raid channel it was a resounding success!! I discovered the hardest part of the entire raid was getting folks together all at the same time and place...and as this was my first time as Raid leader I really appriciate the help of my group leaders and everyone for being patient with my organizational skills..the one thing I can say to anyone else new to this is...get good group leaders who will help with the organization..this is paramount..I was getting tells from group members from the raid channel, from the pu-raid channel, from my guild..I would have lost it without the help of my FANTASTIC group leaders. Thank you all so much!</span></td>
